        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 445 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Brighton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Brighton around 450 PM EDT.
Hartland around 505 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Island Lake State
Recreation Area, Chilson, and Tyrone Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
